Title : Theodore Pileles Doranites
Text : '''Theodore Doranites''' ({{lang-el|Θεόδωρος Δωρανίτης}}; died July 1352) also known as '''Pileles''' (Πιλέλης), was a [[Byzantine Greek]] aristocrat and military leader in the [[Empire of Trebizond]]. A prominent member of the [[Doranites]] aristocratic family from [[Trabzon|Trebizond]], Theodore Doranites was one of the leading figures in the [[Trapezuntine Civil War|civil strife]] that disrupted the Empire in the 14th century. 

Theodore was the brother of the ''[[protovestiarios]]'' [[Constantine Doranites]].{{sfn|PLP|loc=5890. Δωρανίτης Κωνσταντῖνος}} In 1349/50, he held the post of ''[[megas stratopedarches]]'', and with his son and his brother-in-law, was imprisoned for a while due to his rebellious stance against [[Alexios III of Trebizond|Alexios III Megas Komnenos]].{{sfn|PLP|loc=5887. Δωρανίτης Θεόδωρος Πιλέλης}} Released, he was named ''[[protovestiarios]]'' in January 1351, only to be re-arrested and imprisoned in May as a rebel.{{sfn|PLP|loc=5887. Δωρανίτης Θεόδωρος Πιλέλης}} He was finally executed with his son and brother-in-law by strangulation in July 1352.{{sfn|PLP|loc=5887. Δωρανίτης Θεόδωρος Πιλέλης}}

